"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086524","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-18","<p>On 8 March the sale of the former Holloway prison site to social housing group Peabody in partnership with London Square Ltd was announced. The sale will help drive forward the Governmentâs commitment to invest in our prison estate, including to replace ageing prisons with modern, purpose-built establishments, which improve rehabilitation and create safe and secure environments. We have worked closely with the local authority to ensure the amount of affordable housing on the site meets the planning requirement and we are pleased that the proposed development will achieve this aim, while also giving best value to the taxpayer. The money, which was received as a single payment, from this sale forms part of the Departmentâs overall budget and so is supporting our initiatives to deliver safer prisons which better support resettlement and ultimately reduce reoffending.</p><p>The plans for the womenâs centre were set out in the proposals for the site announced by Peabody and London Square who are leading on this important initiative and the development of the site.</p>","Charnwood","Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086524/answer",,,,,"230759 ; 230760 ; 230761 ; 230762 ; 230763 ; 230764","2019-03-18T16:59:14.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086524/answer","Biography information for Edward Argar","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086524/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-11","Women's Centres: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what services will be provided at the womenâs centre to be built on the former site of HMP Holloway.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","230758"
