"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086531","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-03-19","<p>The Ministry of Justice does not hold data on crimes which involve the use of knives or firearms but does collect data on offences on possession of a firearm or a bladed article.</p><p> </p><p>The number of defendants prosecuted and convicted of offences relating to these offences can be found at the following link: <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733981/outcomes-by-offence-tool-2017-update.xlsx" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/733981/outcomes-by-offence-tool-2017-update.xlsx</a>. Search âOffenceâ for `10A Possession of a firearm with intentâ and `10D Possession of article with blade or pointâ.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086531/answer",,,,,"230766 ; 230767 ; 230768 ; 230769 ; 230770 ; 230771 ; 230772 ; 230773 ; 230774 ; 230775 ; 230776","2019-03-19T16:42:50.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086531/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086531/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-03-11","Crimes of Violence: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many convictions there were for (a) crimes involving the use of knives; (b) crimes involving the use of firearms and (c) all violent crimes in 2018.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","230765"
