"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086737","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-14","<p>Permitted development rights for change of use to residential are making an important contribution to the delivery of new homes and have delivered over 46,000 homes to buy or rent in the three years to March 2018. We do not collect information on how many are sold or rented, or on who subsequently lives in them.</p><p>As announced in the written ministerial statement made on 13 March 2019, HCWS1408, we will continue to consider the design of a permitted development right to allow commercial buildings to be demolished and replaced with homes. We also intend to review permitted development rights for conversion of buildings to residential use in respect of the quality standard of homes delivered.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086737/answer",,,,,"230914 ; 230917","2019-03-14T14:53:06.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086737/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086737/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-11","Change of Use","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the number of homeless families housed in temporary accommodation which has been converted into residential use through the permitted development rights process.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","230916"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086738","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-19","<p>The information is not held centrally.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086738/answer",,,,,,"2019-03-19T14:10:54.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086738/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086738/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-11","Hospital Wards: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate he has made of the number of times hospital wards have closed to maintain safe staffing levels for each of the last ten years for which records are available.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","230821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086739","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-14","<p>Permitted development rights for change of use to residential are making an important contribution to the delivery of new homes and have delivered over 46,000 homes to buy or rent in the three years to March 2018. We do not collect information on how many are sold or rented, or on who subsequently lives in them.</p><p>As announced in the written ministerial statement made on 13 March 2019, HCWS1408, we will continue to consider the design of a permitted development right to allow commercial buildings to be demolished and replaced with homes. We also intend to review permitted development rights for conversion of buildings to residential use in respect of the quality standard of homes delivered.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086739/answer",,,,,"230914 ; 230916","2019-03-14T14:53:06.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086739/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1086739/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-11","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate his Department has made of the number of homes delivered through permitted development rights that have been found to not comply with building regulations in each year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","230917"
